Name: Jackson Security Services
Description:
Jackson Electric was founded in 1949 by Tennis and Alma Jackson, and has been a trusted provider of electric and security services in West Alabama for over 65 years. Residential and commercial security services were first introduced as a part of the electric company in 1953. In 1972, Chuck Turner became a partner of Tennis Jackson Electric Company and added alarm system design and installation. In l978 the firm’s security services were separated from the electric side of the house, and in 1982 became Jackson Security Services. That same year JSS purchased Business Security Services in Tuscaloosa.

In 1988, Chuck Turner purchased both the electric and security services and merged the companies. In 1992 Brad Turner was appointed Vice President of Jackson Security Services, and in 2000 Jim Essary was hired as Vice President and General Manager.

In 2014 Jackson Electric Services merged with a similar company in the Tuscaloosa area. Today Jackson Security Services continues in its dedication to West Alabama residential and commercial customers. Jim Essary continues to lead the company as General Manager and Vice President.

Today JSS offers a full range of security options for home or business. Skilled, experienced technicians install the most reliable security systems. Customers can have peace of mind with the guarantee of 24-hour service and protection.

Gate Operator Systems

Name: The Physical Security Group, LLC
Description:
The Physical Security Group (PSG) was established in May 2009, but the core personnel have been together thru a series of acquisitions and takeovers for more than two decades. Initially established in 1990 as part of the Unisys Corporation,  we were awarded the first Army Integrated Commercial Intrusion Detection System (ICIDS-I) and Pentagon Security Contracts.

As the principal security contractor at Ft. Detrick, MD, the Forest Glen Annex, and the Walter Reed Army Institute of Research in Silver Spring, MD.,  PSG is tasked with the maintenance of their existing security systems plus design and installation of new or expanding systems for various tenants. Ft. Detrick is experiencing significant expansion in mission and personnel and PSG is leading the way to meet their security needs.

US Army at more than 80 locations (ICIDS Sites)

Pentagon 
Fort Detrick, MD
US Capitol
US Air Force

Natick Research Lab

Fort Belvoir VA
